    # Mermaid Compatibility

Use Mermaid syntax that renders in both Cursor preview and GitHub.

- Prefer `flowchart TD` or `flowchart LR`.
- For decision edges with labels, use `A -->|label| B`.
- Do not use `A -- label --> B`.
- Avoid alternative labeled-edge forms that are inconsistently supported.
- Keep node IDs simple, put display text in brackets.
- When apostrophes or punctuation are present, quote labels when needed, for example `X["We're Done"]`.

## Example

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    F{Looks Rubbish?}
    G["We're Done"]
    H[Import Excalidraw]
    F -->|No| G
    F -->|Yes| H
```

